[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Fix:** Consider tightening to:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   > That conversation is not happening, and the reason is not that her care team is bad. The cognitive work it requires (integrating nine years of irregular measurements across multiple variables, accounting for treatment effects, factoring in disease-specific progression rates, communicating future-state uncertainty in a way that is actionable on a multi-year horizon) is not what a 20-minute outpatient nephrology visit is structured to do. Each visit is a snapshot. The trajectory lives across snapshots and across an analytic gap that the EHR was never designed to bridge.
